sentence.text: Minichromosome maintenance protein 5 (G1/S transition of mitotic cell cycle) has been suggested overexpressed in cervical cancer, but the clinical value and biological function of MCM5 in cervical cancer is still unknown.

entity.text: G1/S transition of mitotic cell cycle

sentence.text: In our study, G1/S transition of mitotic cell cycle mRNA and protein were significantly overexpressed in cervical cancer tissues and cell lines compared with normal cervical tissues and cell lines, and were obviously increased in cervical adenocarcinoma tissues and cell lines in comparison to cervical squamous cell carcinoma tissues and cell lines.
